As National Parks Month comes to a close, I want to encourage you to take time to visit the incredible parks we have right here in Prince George’s County — and all across our country.

One of our hidden gems is Oxon Cove Park — a peaceful place where you can walk, connect with nature, and even pet the animals. But it's more than just beautiful land. It’s a place with deep, complicated history.

Watch my video below.

Not far from Washington, D.C., this land was once worked by enslaved people. That’s part of our story — and we can't look away from it.

Right now, some are trying to erase uncomfortable truths from our classrooms and communities. But we must tell the full story of our country — the good, the bad, and everything in between — so we can learn, grow, and make sure we never repeat the mistakes of the past.

Our national parks are more than pretty landscapes. They are living classrooms, places of healing, and a reflection of who we are — and who we want to be.

Let’s preserve them, protect them, and make sure they remain a powerful part of our future.

We are working with our state and local partners to counteract these Medicare Cuts on the 60th Anniversary of this life saving program.  We held a town hall in Greenbelt, Maryland with Delegate Ashanti Martinez and healthcare providers to discuss:
H.R. 1, Republican's Big Ugly Bill:
• 331,000 Marylanders will be affected by cuts to Medicaid
• 175,000 Marylanders will lose health care
• 60,000 legal migrants in Maryland will lose health care
• 350 DACA recipients will lose health care
• The state of Maryland will lose $2.7 billion in federal funding annually.

Today’s Medicare Town Hall was more than a policy discussion—it was a wake-up call.

We heard from Sheila Lemus, a constituent living with MS, who survived thanks to Medicaid. But under H.R. 1, folks like Sheila—along with working families, seniors, disabled Americans, and kids with special needs—are being left behind.

This bill guts care when we should be expanding it.

We hosted this dialogue to shine a light on the real consequences of these reckless cuts—and to recommit ourselves to the fight for affordable, accessible health care in Maryland and across the country. 🩺✊🏽

#ProtectMedicare #MedicaidMatters #MD04

I remain dedicated to protecting and strengthening access to affordable healthcare for every American—no matter your age or income.
